{"id":8113,"date":"2023-12-03T20:03:39","date_gmt":"2023-12-03T20:03:39","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/?p=8113"},"modified":"2023-12-04T14:12:42","modified_gmt":"2023-12-04T14:12:42","slug":"what-divorce-settlement-am-i-entitled-to","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/what-divorce-settlement-am-i-entitled-to\/","title":{"rendered":"What Divorce Settlement Am I Entitled To?"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"410\" data-id=\"8114\" src=\"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/divorce-7526848_1280-1024x410.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8114\" srcset=\"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/divorce-7526848_1280-1024x410.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/divorce-7526848_1280-300x120.jpg 300w, https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/divorce-7526848_1280-768x307.jpg 768w, https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/divorce-7526848_1280.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<span class=\"gdlr-core-space-shortcode\" style=\"margin-top: 30px ;\"  ><\/span>\n\n\n\n<p>Each divorce settlement is unique and depends on various factors, including your personal circumstances, assets, and the presence of children.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Going through a divorce can be a challenging and emotional time. One of the key aspects that many individuals are concerned about is the divorce settlement. You may be wondering, &#8220;What am I entitled to during the divorce process?&#8221;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s important to understand that in the UK, there is no specific formula to determine who is entitled to which assets. The courts consider several criteria, known as section 25 criteria, and prioritize the needs of dependent children in the settlement. This process aims to ensure a fair outcome for both parties involved, taking into account the contributions each partner made during the marriage, both financially and non-financially.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Key Takeaways<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Divorce settlements vary based on personal circumstances and assets.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>The UK courts use section 25 criteria to determine a fair distribution.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dependent children&#8217;s needs are prioritized in the settlement process.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Types of Divorce Settlements<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When going through a divorce, it&#8217;s essential to understand the types of divorce settlements you may be entitled to. This will help you make informed decisions about how to proceed with your case. In the UK, there are two primary types of financial orders you can apply for: the <strong>Consent Order<\/strong> and the <strong>Clean Break Order<\/strong>. Both orders deal with financial matters during a divorce and aid in providing clarity for the future.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Consent Order<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A<a href=\"https:\/\/www.gov.uk\/money-property-when-relationship-ends\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\"> Consent Order<\/mark><\/a> is a legally binding document that outlines the financial arrangements agreed upon by both parties during a divorce. This may include the division of assets such as:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Property (e.g., the family home, other properties)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Savings and investments<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pensions<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Income (including salaries, bonuses, and commissions)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The Consent Order is submitted to the court for approval, and once approved, it becomes legally binding. This ensures that both parties adhere to the agreed-upon financial arrangements. It is crucial to have this document drafted by a legal expert to avoid potential complications or future financial claims.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Clean Break Order<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A<a href=\"https:\/\/www.mplaw.co.uk\/insights\/news\/uk-divorce-financial-settlements-guide\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\"> Clean Break Order<\/mark><\/a> is another type of financial order that can be requested during divorce proceedings. This order effectively severs all financial ties between the parties, meaning there will be no ongoing maintenance payments or any future claims on each other&#8217;s assets.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Key points to consider about Clean Break Orders include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>They eliminate any future financial claims from either party<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>They may not always be suitable, particularly in cases where there are children or a significant disparity in the parties&#8217; incomes<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are considering a divorce, it is essential to seek professional advice from a solicitor or a specialist in family law to determine which financial order is most suitable for your circumstances. This will help ensure a fair and legally binding settlement that protects your future financial interests.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Determining Factors for Entitlement<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When assessing what you are entitled to in a divorce settlement, there are several factors the court considers. In this section, we will discuss the three main factors: Marriage Duration, Financial Contributions, and Future Needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Marriage Duration<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The length of your marriage has a significant impact on the entitlement in a divorce settlement. Generally, longer marriages result in more equal division of assets, whereas shorter marriages may lead more towards separating what each party brought into the marriage. However, individual circumstances may vary, and the court will consider other factors as well.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Financial Contributions<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Financial contributions during the marriage play a key role in determining the entitlement in a divorce settlement. This includes direct contributions (e.g., salaries) and indirect contributions (e.g., raising children or maintaining the household). The court evaluates the overall <strong><em>contributions<\/em><\/strong> of each party, considering factors such as:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Income, property, and other financial resources<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Contributions to the welfare of the family, including child-caring and homemaking<a href=\"https:\/\/koala.sh\/article?articleId=08412926-b98f-4faf-b3f3-e3d996ea3187#user-content-fn-1%5E\"><sup>1<\/sup><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Future Needs<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another crucial factor is the <strong>future needs<\/strong> of each party. The court aims to ensure that the divorce settlement addresses the necessary financial resources for both parties to meet their <a href=\"https:\/\/koala.sh\/article?articleId=08412926-b98f-4faf-b3f3-e3d996ea3187#user-content-fn-2%5E\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">future needs<\/mark><\/a>. To assess these needs, the court will evaluate factors such as:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Age, physical and mental health<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Standard of living during the marriage<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ability to earn, property and <a href=\"https:\/\/koala.sh\/article?articleId=08412926-b98f-4faf-b3f3-e3d996ea3187#user-content-fn-3%5E\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">financial resources<\/mark><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>In summary, the entitlement in a divorce settlement depends on a range of factors, including the marriage duration, financial contributions, and future needs of both parties. Each case is assessed individually, and the court considers all relevant factors as they strive to reach a fair and just outcome.Looking for the best <a href=\"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/divorce\/\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">divorce solicitors Lebanon<\/mark><\/a>? Get in touch with SG Murphy Solicitors now!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<span class=\"gdlr-core-space-shortcode\" style=\"margin-top: 30px ;\"  ><\/span>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Each divorce settlement is unique and depends on various factors, including your personal circumstances, assets, and the presence of children. Going through a divorce can be a challenging and emotional time. One of the key aspects that many individuals are concerned about is the divorce settlement. You may be wondering, &#8220;What am I entitled to [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8114,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_monsterinsights_sitenote_category":0,"footnotes":""},"categories":[2,3],"tags":[49,50],"class_list":["post-8113","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-blog","category-masonry","tag-d